<br>
Killing people?  Taking over the world?  Raping women?  Style?<br>
<br>
What REALLY makes a villian evil?<br>
<br>
<br>
In my opinion it's definately something to do with style.  Just look at Sephiroth?  They have style.  Anyone can kill anybody, but it doesn't make them evil, unless you do it with a certain bordering psychotic style... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=prismrefraction>PrismRefraction</A> at: 9/15/02 4:56:34 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uspikescafe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SpikesCafe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.spikescafe.com/shell.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gamera <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/14/02 7:38:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.spikescafe.com/spikes/spike8.gif width=128 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The evil...</span><hr size=1> Fluffy cat. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/14/02 8:42:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The evil...</span><hr size=1> Which Alucard? I'm guessing it's not from SOTN, considering he's not evil.<br>
<br>
Anyway, what makes someone evil? Not some mindless killing machine, but someone who KNOWS right from wrong, but does what he/she wants anyway. Someone that completely disregards the interests of others in favor of themself. That doesn't necessarily make a GOOD villain, but I'd say they'd be the most evil. Style really has nothing to do with how evil they are, but it certainly makes them a better character. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=neoangel>NeoAngel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/15/02 8:41:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The evil...</span><hr size=1> In real life the only thing that makes a person evil is when his beliefs conflict with your beliefs, and evilness is just a matter of opinion. For example, NATO etc considers people like Bin Laden and Saddam evil, but they consider us just as evil.<br>
In an anime or manga, what makes a character evil is when his views or beliefs conflict with the main character's beliefs, unless he is the main character. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/15/02 9:34:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The evil...</span><hr size=1> Not really. A difference of opinion doesn't make someone evil. Maybe if their morality was vastly different from the morality of the majority, you'd consider him evil, but that's not the same thing at all. A group of non evil characters could all have a difference in views on life, yet not be evil. And what if the villain is the main character? <br>
<br>
And character MIGHT be evil because his views are different from the main character's, but it's not really what defines a character as such. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=prismrefraction>PrismRefraction</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/15/02 4:55:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The evil...</span><hr size=1> Bin Laden is more of a radical freedom fighter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gloommouse>GloomMouse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/16/02 6:20:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evil</span><hr size=1> The best example of real evil is Kain from Legacy of Kain: Blood Omen 1 &amp; 2 (Not those stupid Soul Reaver Games)<br>
Evil does not require style, but it sure is neat... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=neoangel>NeoAngel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/16/02 11:51:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evil</span><hr size=1> OK, so it's a combination of your morals and your actions that lead to you being labelled as evil. I was wrong, and I'm admitting this (One for the photo books people, this rarely happens!)<br>
<br>
Apparantly, many people wind up preferring the villain to the hero of a manga. Isn't that wierd? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=prismrefraction>PrismRefraction</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/16/02 12:31:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evil</span><hr size=1> The mind and motivations of the villian are both quite interesting, take for example Yu-gi-oh, Pegasus is like the way he is because of his wife dying.  Sephiroth loses it because when he learns of his true origins and understands.  Magus of Chrono Trigger had a really good reason, to take down Lavos for vengence. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/16/02 2:23:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evil</span><hr size=1> I don't know that I completely agree about Kain. He's certainly no saint, but what about him was so different from any other hero in a game? His overall goal was not evil, and the end of the game was your own decision. You could choose to sacrifice yourself or to become an evil ruler. I suppose Blood Omen 2 goes on the assumption that he chose the latter (since they do in the Soul Reaver games), but that was one outcome, and even that doesn't necessarily make him evil (as they've hinted at in the Soul Reaver games).<br>
<br>
If you think about it, what has he done that's so much more horrible than other characters in games? He killed to accomplish his goal, but even Link does that. Again, his overall goal was not evil. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=prismrefraction>PrismRefraction</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/16/02 6:15:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evil</span><hr size=1> True true, but they do it for different reasons of course as you know.  Link does it for others, well most of the time, so the world can be saved and everything will be sunshine and lolly pops all day long forever and ever. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/16/02 7:40:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evil</span><hr size=1> I'm not saying he's GOOD. Not at all. I just think he fits into more of a grey area. His actions, at least in the first game, were for the good of Nosgoth. Of course, he was doing it for his own reasons, that was just incidental to him. But he wasn't just roaming around randomly killing people either. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chaser226>chaser226</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/16/02 7:45:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evil</span><hr size=1> evil.... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chaser226>chaser226</A> at: 9/16/02 7:45:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gloommouse>GloomMouse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/18/02 9:55:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evil</span><hr size=1> hmmm... I suppose Kain is really more a character of true neutrality, maybe slipping into selfish evil from time to time... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uretrotorque.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RetroTorque</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/19/02 9:03:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/solidnate/sig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The evil...</span><hr size=1> True evil is Hannibal Lecter.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/umercurialme.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mercurial Me</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/19/02 4:54:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/anyte/misc/scrn5.jpg x=100 y=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The evil...</span><hr size=1> Shira - Blade of the Immortal - evil evil evil.  What makes him evil?  His acts of cruelty and sadism bring him great joy.  He commits the most heinous acts without any remorse.<br>
<br>
He kills a dog that a girl befriends ... offers some to the girl and has her believe that it is some other kind of meat ... when he lets her know what she has eaten he roars with laughter ...<br>
<br>
He attacks and cuts pieces of a woman's body off, rapes her, and leaves her to die a slow and painful death ... and to him it was exciting ... entertaining even ...<br>
<br>
Shira is evil.  He does what he does to his own benefit without care or concern for others.  He laughs at your pain, whether he is the cause of your pain or whether someone else is responsible. <br>
<br>
He can't be trusted ... he'll allow you to believe anything ... only to get what he wants .... and what happens to you is of no concern to him.  If something bad happens to you it makes him feel good ... not bad.<br>
<br>
evil evil evil <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=1948.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=1948.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1948.topic&index=15><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=1948.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.threadControl?topicID=1948.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1948.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1948.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="polykarbonbbsfrm18">PK-BBS Rules and Regulations!<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm27">Board F.A.Q.s<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm3">News and Updates<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm2">Photoshop and Art questions<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm4">General Manga/Anime Discussion<option value="polyka